gujarati.context:
After from Kutch, a merciful one came; 
From Panchal, a wretched one arrived;
With companions I took two chariots, the first to arrive in this land now.

Here is the translation:

God's darshan was gone, merciful one; came to Changa village without a share of compassion; 
The devotee did not write the written account, taken away from there, reached Rojni gam with my mother at 25.

This is the translation:

This was consumed by eight directions, then the whole universe was filled; 
Whatever dharma was given, even that was taken back with retribution, in accordance with Vedic principle.

Here is the translation:

Eat well and enjoy your beauty, but don't preserve your path; 
Thus perished, our king knew his heart's majesty.
